Pending packaging follow-ups
============================

Repack candidates for +dfsg
---------------------------

Only what actually violates the DFSG. Everything else (Windows-only C++
modules, PowerShell scripts, .psd asset sources, Visio docs, .nuspec
templates, .NET helpers) can stay in orig.tar without consequence since
it is not compiled, installed, or otherwise exposed by the agent-only
Debian build.

Must remove (DFSG #2 - precompiled binary without source in the tarball):
  installers/installer-NSCP/wixca.dll        PE32 DLL, no source shipped
  libs/protobuf_net/Google.Protobuf.dll      PE32 .NET assembly, no source shipped

Review before next repack (borderline, not a hard blocker):
  include/clr/clr_scoped_ptr.hpp             CC-BY-SA-3.0 with extra
                                             "GPL section 7" attribution
                                             clauses; DFSG-compliant in
                                             practice but Creative Commons
                                             is discouraged for software.
                                             Windows-only (CLR), so dropping
                                             it costs nothing on Linux.

  docs/source/realtime-monitoring.vsdx       Microsoft Visio file. The vsdx
                                             container is open XML inside,
                                             so not strictly DFSG-blocking,
                                             but it is editable only with
                                             Visio in practice and never
                                             installed - safe to drop.

